In this article, Governor McMaster of South Carolina and President Trump address the ongoing disaster caused by Hurricane Florence. They discuss the record-breaking amounts of rain that have fallen in the state and the imminent threat of flooding. Both leaders express their confidence in the coordination and cooperation between federal, state, and local authorities, as well as the support from the community. They assure the people of South Carolina that the federal government is fully committed to providing assistance and resources for the recovery and rebuilding process. General Livingston also speaks, highlighting the efforts of Team South Carolina in evacuations, search and rescue operations, and infrastructure preparation. Director Webster emphasizes the unprecedented challenge of the flooding and the determination of the team to save lives and protect property. The article concludes with President Trump reiterating his support and commitment to the people of South Carolina.